---
title: "_call (Caller)"
---
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB
    [*] --> q_call: (success, response) = target.call(data)
    q_call --> q_check_success: evaluate success
    q_check_success --> q_return: success == true
    q_check_success --> q_check_response: success == false
    q_check_response --> q_bubble_revert: response.length > 0
    q_check_response --> q_revert_generic: response.length == 0
    q_bubble_revert --> [*]: revert(response)
    q_revert_generic --> [*]: revert LowLevelCallFailed()
    q_return --> [*]: return response

    note right of q_call
        INV-001: target receives exact calldata without modification
        INV-002: return value is raw bytes from external call
    end note

    note right of q_check_response
        INV-003: failed calls always revert - never return silently
        INV-004: original revert reason is preserved when response.length > 0
    end note
